Standards Alignment Overview
This system is designed to operate inside existing emergency‑management doctrine.
It aligns with ICS, NIMS, CAP, EDXL, and NIEM without replacing or overriding any of them.
Where standards lack required structures (e.g., cascades, lineage), the system extends them without breaking interoperability.

Component‑to‑Standard Mapping
Lineage Engine
ICS: Aligns with ICS‑214 (Activity Log) and ICS‑202/203 documentation lineage.

NIMS: Aligns with NIMS “Information Management” and “Resource Tracking.”

CAP: No equivalent (CAP has no provenance model).

EDXL: Partial alignment with EDXL‑DE metadata.

NIEM: Aligns with NIEM metadata/audit components.

Notes: Novel capability; requires NIEM/EDXL extension.

Gravitational Alignment Model
ICS/NIMS: Conceptual alignment with chain‑of‑command and unity‑of‑command.

CAP/EDXL/NIEM: No equivalents.

Notes: Pure internal safety mechanism.

Cascade Logic (Disaster‑Chain Model)
ICS: Aligns with ICS‑209/215 documentation of cascading impacts.

NIMS: Aligns with situational assessment doctrine.

CAP: Cannot express cascades.

EDXL: Partial alignment with SitRep/RM.

NIEM: Representable via structured relationships.

Notes: Major innovation; requires schema extension.

Context‑Gradient Assessment
ICS: Aligns with ICS‑209 severity indicators.

NIMS: Aligns with situational assessment.

CAP: Severity/urgency/certainty fields only (no gradients).

EDXL: Severity fields only.

NIEM: Can encode gradients.

Notes: Extension beyond all standards.

IRD/RRD Reporting
ICS: Direct alignment with ICS‑201/202/209.

NIMS: Fully aligned with reporting cadence.

CAP: Not applicable.

EDXL: Aligns with SitRep and DE envelopes.

NIEM: Expressible via IEPDs.

Notes: Fully standards‑aligned.

Human‑Command Enforcement
ICS: Direct alignment with chain‑of‑command doctrine.

NIMS: Aligns with unity‑of‑command and management by objectives.

CAP/EDXL/NIEM: Not applicable.

Notes: Internal safeguard.

Data Ingestion + Normalization
ICS: Maps ICS forms into structured fields.

NIMS: Aligns with information management.

CAP: Direct alignment for alert ingestion.

EDXL: Direct alignment for RM/SitRep/DE.

NIEM: Direct alignment via IEPDs.

Notes: Standards‑aligned.

Situational Synthesis Layer
ICS: Aligns with ICS‑209 and planning cycle.

NIMS: Aligns with situational assessment.

CAP: Not applicable.

EDXL: Partial alignment with SitRep.

NIEM: Representable.

Notes: Internal logic.
